title: Drawing, "Female Head, Left Profile, in Headdress"
description: The angular profile of forehead, nose, closed mouth, and chin is depicted in dark outline backed by shading. A barely outlined headdress incorporates waves of chin-length hair framing the face. Lettering is inscribed across the top of the page and just below the outline of the headdress at the top.

tombstone.epitaph:
Drawing, "Female Head, Left Profile, in Headdress".
14.8 x 12.5 cm (5 7/8 x 4 15/16 in.). Gift of Ellen Gustav Jensen. 1956-47-131.
